Kolhapur police looking out for persons who damaged set of Sanjay Leela Bhansaliâ€™s Padmavati 
15-3-2017 
Kolhapur police are looking out for unidentified persons, who allegedly damaged shooting set of Rani Padmavati, directed by Sanjay Leela Bhansali, near Panhala fort in Kolhapur district.

According to preliminary reports, a group of unidentified persons damaged set of Rani Padmavati and also vehicles parked outside. Incident came to light when shooting team reached spot this morning. Extent of damage is yet to be estimated

Police have reached the spot. It was not known whether formal complaint has-been lodged.

Bhansali shifted to a spot near historic fort in Panhala for shooting of Rani Padmavati after he was staunchly opposed in Jaipur few months back. Bhansali was even slapped by youths, objecting certain references in the movie.

Shooting of Rani Padmavati is in progress at Panhala for last two weeks. 
